radiographic_examinations.findings: Fluid-filled and dilated appendix measuring up to 9 mm in maximum diameter, mild enhancing appendiceal wall thickening with mild adjacent periappendiceal fat stranding, gastric bypass changes with suture lines in the left hemi-abdomen, possible gastro-gastric fistula, small bilateral subcentimeter renal hypodensities, no hydronephrosis, mild amount of free fluid in the cul-de-sac, no free air, mild multilevel degenerative changes in the thoracic and lumbar spine.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Subcentimeter calcification in the lateral segment of the left hepatic lobe is stable since earlier evaluation, likely representing granuloma.
